abstract: Fractures are growing among both Democrats and Republicans.
snippet: Fractures are growing among both Democrats and Republicans.
lead_paragraph: In case you haven’t noticed, long-established political parties across the democratic world are blowing up, with Britain’s Labour Party just the latest to fracture. Could America’s parties be next?

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: After shifting the Democratic Party to the left, Bernie Sanders could struggle to beat a crop of fresh-faced candidates who support many of the policies he championed.

abstract: A glossary for the emerging Democratic health care debate.
snippet: A glossary for the emerging Democratic health care debate.
lead_paragraph: Democrats, the many running for president as well as energized members of Congress, are talking big about health care again. Among other things, that means brace yourself for some jargon.

abstract: Mr. Short, who was President Trump’s legislative affairs director for about two years, is taking the job vacated by Nick Ayers.
snippet: Mr. Short, who was President Trump’s legislative affairs director for about two years, is taking the job vacated by Nick Ayers.
lead_paragraph: Vice President Mike Pence has chosen Marc Short, who served as President Trump’s legislative affairs director for most of his first two years in office, to be his chief of staff, a person familiar with the announcement said Tuesday.
